definition:
ὁμοίωμα, -τος, τό
 (ὁμοιόω), [in LXX for דְּמוּת, תַּבְנִית, תְּמוּנָה, etc. ;] 
that which is made like something; 
   (a) concrete, an image, like­ness (Psa.106:20, Eze.1:5, 1Ma.3:48, al.) : Rev.9:7; 
   (b) abstract, like­ness, resemblance: Rom.5:14 6:5 8:3, Php.2:7; ἐν ὁ. εἰκόνος, Rom.1:23.†
 SYN.: εἰκών (which see), ὁμοίωσις  (AS)
